quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  69,38,"Now, I do swear by whatever you see"
  69,39,and whatever you cannot see
  69,40,"Indeed, this Ë¹QuranËº is the recitation of a noble Messenger"
  69,41,"It is not the prose of a poet Ë¹as you claimËº, Ë¹yetËº you hardly have any faith"
  69,42,"Nor is it the mumbling of a fortune-teller, Ë¹yetËº you are hardly mindful"
  69,43,Ë¹It isËº a revelation from the Lord of all worlds
  69,44,Had the Messenger made up something in Our Name
  69,45,We would have certainly seized him by his right hand
  69,46,then severed his aorta
  69,47,and none of you could have shielded him Ë¹from UsËº
  69,48,"Indeed, this Ë¹QuranËº is a reminder to those mindful Ë¹of AllahËº"
  69,49,And We certainly know that some of you will persist in denial
  69,50,and it will surely be a source of regret for the disbelievers
  69,51,"And indeed, this Ë¹QuranËº is the absolute truth"
  69,52,"So glorify the Name of your Lord, the Greatest"